               <head>Grant; Higham; 1381</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111663">Higham</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1381">1381</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Crowe</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Hiegham)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Chippeleye</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Chippeleye">
                           <forename>Katherine</forename> his wife</persName>, of the tenements and lands once held by the said Robert of the gift of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> of <surname>Chippeleye</surname></persName>, in Hiegham.
                        Dated, at <placeName role="date" key="place_111663">Higham (Hiegham)</placeName> on Monday [24 June] the feast of the nativity of St John Baptist, 5 Ric. II [1381].
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Hiegham</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Colet</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Pikchese</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Ilger</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Aumener</surname></persName>, and others.
                        Endorsed: Carta fact' Will'mo Chyppeley deten' in Heigham in Lortland [?].
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
